{"title_page": "Jean-Marc Savelli", "text_new": "{{cleanup rewrite|date=December 2013}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name              = Jean-Marc Savelli\n\n| image             = [[File:Jean Marc SAVELLI Pianist.jpg|thumb|Jean-Marc SAVELLI prepare his album]]\n| image_size        = \n| alt               = \n| caption           = \n| birth_date        = {{Birth date|1955|10|18|df=y}}\n| birth_place       = [[Mulhouse]], [[Alsace]], France\n| death_date        = \n| death_place       = \n| background        = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| genre             = [[Classical music|Classical]]\n| occupation        = Pianist\n| instrument        = [[Piano]] \n| years_active      = <!-- YYYY\u2013YYYY (or \u2013present) -->\n|official website   =|url = http://www.jmsavelli.com/}}\n\n'''Jean-Marc Savelli''' (born 18 October 1955) is a French [[pianist]].<ref name=\"jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange_c\">{{cite web|url=http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/jean-marc%20savelli_biographie.pdf |title=Jean Marc Savelli : Resume |publisher=Jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>\n\nKnown by the general public for his interpretations<ref name=\"youtube_a\">{{YouTube|_bZm1P9EeSU|JM Savelli plays the pr\u00e9lude 2 opus 3}} de [[Sergue\u00ef Rachmaninov]] \u00e0 la [[salle Gaveau]]</ref> of works from [[Franz Liszt]]<ref name=\"youtube_b\">{{YouTube|vSe_MZ0khKI|JM Savelli plays \"R\u00eave d'amour\"}} de Franz Liszt \u00e0 la [[salle Gaveau]] (Paris)</ref><ref name=\"chaumiereonline\">{{cite web |url=http://www.chaumiereonline.com/Musique-Classique/Page-Resultat-Recherche.aspx?type=1&rch=savelli |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-08-31 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130102120346/http://www.chaumiereonline.com/Musique-Classique/Page-Resultat-Recherche.aspx?type=1&rch=savelli |archivedate=2013-01-02 }}</ref><ref name=\"youtube_c\">{{YouTube|IaCGavCd1-s|JM Savelli joue \"Les fun\u00e9railles\" de Franz Liszt}}</ref> and [[Frederic Chopin]], Jean-Marc Savelli<ref name=\"ladepeche\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ladepeche.fr/article/2000/08/09/142108-le-cabardes-va-piano.html |title=Le Cabard\u00e8s va piano - 09/08/2000 |publisher=Ladepeche.fr |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref> also distinguished himself in the classical repertoire with [[Johann Sebastian Bach]] and [[Ludwig van Beethoven]], and in the Impressionist repertoire of [[Claude Debussy]].<ref name=\"jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange\">{{cite web|url=http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr |title=recital JM SAVELLI Pianiste-Concertiste le virtuose de l'Emotion |publisher=Jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nBorn in [[Mulhouse]], [[Alsace]], France, from an Alsatian mother, Marie-Louise Schreyer, (herself coming by her mother from a family of travelling musicians who performed in Eastern Europe, including in front of the Imperial Court of [[Russia]], before settling in Alsace in the Lower Rhine), and a Corsican father, Gratien Savelli, met on the hazard of the Second World War, who often was singing  \"lamentus\" Corsicans songs as well as other traditional Corsican songs. Established with his wife in Mulhouse, he nevertheless remained nostalgic for his native [[Corsica]].\n\nJM Savelli, soaked in this environment,  is registered at the age of 8 years by his parents at the National Conservatory of Music and Dramatic Art of Mulhouse beside Suzanne Muller-Gunst, [[piano]] teacher, who had wished, upon JM SAVELLI granting of the first prize at the Conservatoire National de Musique de Mulhouse, that Jean-Marc SAVELLI (first prize that he had obtained at the age of 12 years from a unanimous jury) could continue his studies at the National Conservatory of Music [[Basel]] ([[Switzerland]]).\n\nAfterwards this is [[Paris]] and the Master [[Pierre Sancan]],<ref name=\"musimem\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musimem.com/prix-rome-1940-1949.htm |title=Prix de Rome 1940-1949 |publisher=Musimem.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref> French pianist, that his parents choose, so that he could continue his musical studies, and prepare to join the Conservatoire National Superieur de Musique in Paris (CNSMD)(''[[Conservatoire de Paris]]'').<ref name=\"jmsavelli\">{{cite web|url=http://www.jmsavelli.com/ |title=recital JM SAVELLI Pianiste-Concertiste le virtuose de l'Emotion |publisher=Jmsavelli.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>\nHe succeeded his entrance exam and entered the class of [[Monique de La Bruchollerie]],<ref name=\"jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange_d\">{{cite web |url=http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/MOT_DE_M_LA_BRUCHOLLERIE_SUR_DIPLOME_JMSAVELLI.pdf |title=Orange |publisher=Jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06 }}{{Dead link|date=February 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> French international pianist, whose great career was abruptly stopped following a car accident.\n\nMonique de la Bruchollerie died, it was a cataclysm for all students, especially for Jean-Marc Savelli who was very close to the personality of his master to whom he will make a final tribute, carrying her coffin with other of her students.\n\nFrench international pianist [[Yvonne Lef\u00e9bure]],<ref>[http://tmedeffrstagingmediasupload_FICHIERdocmt78.medef.fr/staging/medias/upload/67731_FICHIER.doc ]{{dead link|date=June 2015}}</ref> took over her formation.\n\n==Career==\nAfter a series of concerts in the world,<ref name=\"musique-corse\">{{cite web|url=http://www.musique-corse.com/cat.php?idcat=97 |title=Corse, musique en Corse, vente disques de musique corse |publisher=Musique-corse.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>  Jean Marc Savelli momentarily has stopped his career but not the piano, for family reasons, but he has continued to practice piano.<ref name=\"medecines-douces\">{{cite web|url=http://medecines-douces.eu/therapie/content/musicoth%C3%A9rapie-musico-stressologie-et-grand-pr%C3%A9matur%C3%A9 |title=Musicoth\u00e9rapie, Musico-Stressologie et Grand Pr\u00e9matur\u00e9 &#124; Th\u00e9rapies Int\u00e9gratives, Hypnose Ericksonienne, Ost\u00e9opathie, Sophrologie, Paris |publisher=Medecines-douces.eu |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>\nIt was during this time that he devoted to the influence of music on people,<ref name=\"affinitiz\">{{cite web|url=http://affinitiz.net/space/aecouterelax/content/_FDD880A5-F325-4D48-BB23-D159DC98D232 |accessdate=August 20, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131111162704/http://affinitiz.net/space/aecouterelax/content/_FDD880A5-F325-4D48-BB23-D159DC98D232 |archivedate=November 11, 2013 }}</ref> and primarily for those who suffer.<ref name=\"jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange_b\">{{cite web |url=http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/affiche_2005_sorbonne_conference_nouvelle_adresse.pdf |title=Orange |publisher=Jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06 }}{{Dead link|date=February 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nHe embodies his research with the help of doctors, by the establishment of an emotional level, usable by anyone other than the musicians.<ref name=\"medecines-douces_a\">{{cite web|url=http://medecines-douces.eu/therapie/content/la-musico-stressologie%C2%A9-cr%C3%A9%C3%A9e-par-j-m-savelli |title=La Musico-Stressologie\u00a9 cr\u00e9\u00e9e par J-M. Savelli &#124; Th\u00e9rapies Int\u00e9gratives, Hypnose Ericksonienne, Ost\u00e9opathie, Sophrologie, Paris |publisher=Medecines-douces.eu |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>\nSince 2012, Jean Marc Savelli prepares his coming back of concerts devoted to Beethoven-Chopin-Liszt. He is expected back on scene in 2013.\n\n2013 He comes back with an original video clip \"Corse Classique\" dedicated to [[Ludwig van Beethoven]], [[Franz Liszt]], [[Frederic Chopin]],<ref>{{YouTube|id=gXIChwW9vOA#t=148|title=\"Corse Classique\", produced by the studio Ricordu}}</ref> VOTED BEST YOUTUBE VIDEO about [[Ludwig van Beethoven]] by music sense.org <ref name=\"musicsense.org\">{{cite web|url=http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/musicsense.org.jpg |title=Beethoven - Emotion Classique |publisher=Musicsense.org |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref> for the interpretation of Jean-Marc SAVELLI of the [[Piano Sonata No. 8 (Beethoven)|Piano Sonata No. 8]] (\"Path\u00e9tique\") of [[Ludwig van Beethoven]]\n\n2014 he presents his new album \"CLASSICAL RECITAL\", (American) Label \"FAMOUS RECORDS CORP\" <ref name=\"famousmusicgroup.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.famousmusicgroup.com/ |title=famous-records |publisher=Famousmusicgroup.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140810012308/http://www.famousmusicgroup.com/ |archive-date=2014-08-10 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref name=\"amazon.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Classical-Recital-Jean-Marc-Savelli/dp/B00LBUVT9Y |title=Classical Recital: Jean-Marc Savelli: MP3 Downloads |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref>\n\nThe website \"zippyshare\" positioned Jean-Marc in the TOP 1000 artists playing Beethoven and placing Jean-Marc Savelli between Wilhelm Kempff and Vladimir Horowitz,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.zippyshare.eu/genre.php?title=beethoven |title=beethoven Music Genre - Zippy Download Free ZippyShare Mp3 Download |publisher=ZippyShare.eu |accessdate=2015-06-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150105132602/http://www.zippyshare.eu/genre.php?title=beethoven# |archive-date=2015-01-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref> \nand NUMBER ONE in the TOP 1000 for his performances in [[Franz Liszt]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.zippyshare.eu/genre.php?title=liszt |title=liszt Music Genre - Zippy Download Free ZippyShare Mp3 Download |publisher=ZippyShare.eu |accessdate=2015-06-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150105132614/http://www.zippyshare.eu/genre.php?title=liszt# |archive-date=2015-01-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/jms_n1%20liszt.JPG</ref>\n\nAlso ranked in the TOP 12 GLOBAL PIANISTS Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Chopin interpreters by edu.gazeta.pl.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edu.gazeta.pl/edu/h/Pianista |title=Pianista - w encyklopedii online |language=pl |publisher=Edu.gazeta.pl |date= |accessdate=2015-06-06}}</ref><ref>http://jeanmarc.savelli.pagesperso-orange.fr/jm_savelli.JPG</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n1989 ALBUM,<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fptgeBULc5g&list=OLAK5uy_m3eYQ3AENODsPUofKLejsbc-n8bbX8Pf4</ref> \nAlbum archived on the famous National Library of France (\"Biblioth\u00e8que Nationale de France\" BNF)<ref>https://data.bnf.fr/fr/13962815/jean-marc_savelli/</ref>\n\n[[Fr\u00e9d\u00e9ric Chopin]] \n* Mazurka No 1 op 7\n* Mazurka n\u00b02 op7\n* Mazurka n\u00b04 op17\n* Mazurka n\u00b02 op68\n* Mazurka n\u00b04 op67\n* Polonaise n\u00b01 op26\n* Polonaise n\u00b01 op40\n* Polonaise n\u00b02 op40\n* Polonaise in A-flat major, Op. 53 \"Heroic Polonaise\"  <ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=liODMUIXUtI</ref>\n* Pr\u00e9lude No. 15 op 28\n* Pr\u00e9lude No. 4 op 28\n\n[[Ludwig van Beethoven]]\n* Piano Sonata No. 8 in C minor, Op. 13, commonly known as Sonata Path\u00e9tique\n* 1st movement <ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uIzJE8o2QZo</ref>\n* 2nd movement <ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=l81BAZgSCUE</ref>\n* 3rd movement  <ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TY2wYBm2AFw</ref>\n\n[[Sergei Rachmaninov]]\n* Pr\u00e9lude No. 2 op 3 <ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_bZm1P9EeSU</ref>\n\n[[Franz Liszt]]\n* Fun\u00e9railles n\u00b05 <ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IaCGavCd1-s</ref>\n* Rhapsodie hongroise n\u00b02 <ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NMAUDorDlNk</ref>\n* Mephisto Walse n\u00b01\n\n[[Robert Schumann]]\n* Reverie\n\n2014 album \"CLASSICAL RECITAL\", on label \"FAMOUS RECORDS Corp\" <ref name=\"famousmusicgroup.com\"/><ref name=\"amazon.com\"/><ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JJXnAyICU34&list=OLAK5uy_nRnuwzKgFSSyDydYcG0uxMW6